[[File:Jean Auguste Dominique Ingres - Double Portrait of Otto Magnus von Stackelberg and Jacob Linckh - WGA11856.jpg|right|thumb|Doppelportrait of Jacob Linckh and Otto Magnus von Stackelberg by [[Jean-Auguste-Dominique Ingres]].]]
'''Jakob Linckh''' (1786<ref name="unil">[http://www.unil.ch/esag/page26236.html Cockerell and the "Grand Tour"]</ref> or 14 November 1787<ref name="von Buerkel">Ludwig von Buerkel, ''Münchner Jahrbuch der bildenden kunst'', vol. 12, Prestel Verlag, 1970, page 137.</ref><ref>[[Virtual International Authority File|VIAF]]: "Linckh, Jakob 1787-1841"</ref> &ndash; 1841) was a German painter and archaeologist, born in [[Bad Cannstatt|Cannstatt]].<ref name="von Buerkel"></ref>

In 1810–11, he accompanied [[Charles Robert Cockerell]], [[John Foster (architect)|John Foster]], [[Carl Haller von Hallerstein]] and [[Otto Magnus von Stackelberg (archaeologist)|Otto Magnus von Stackelberg]] on their expeditions to the temples of [[Temple of Aphaia|Aphaia]] on [[Aegina]] and of [[Apollo]] at [[Bassae]].  On this trip he also drew a plan of the ancient theatre at [[Eretria]].<ref name="unil"></ref>

